text:
The treaty with Vibhíshaṇ made:
The plan for Rávaṇ’s slaughter laid. How Kumbhakarṇa in his pride
And Meghanáda fought and died. How Rávaṇ in the fight was slain,
And captive Sítá brought again. Vibhíshaṇ set upon the throne;
The flying chariot Pushpak shown. How Brahmá and the Gods appeared,
And Sítá’s doubted honour cleared. How in the flying car they rode
To Bharadvája’s cabin abode. The Wind-God’s son sent on afar;
How Bharat met the flying car. How Ráma then was king ordained;
The legions their discharge obtained. How Ráma cast his queen away;
How grew the people’s love each day. Thus did the saint Válmíki tell
Whate’er in Ráma’s life befell,
And in the closing verses all
That yet to come will once befall.
